## ğŸ“ Exam-Ready Short Answer (5 lines)

Indian cricket is governed by the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI). The India national cricket team represents the country in Test, ODI, and T20 formats. India has won major tournaments like the 1983 and 2011 Cricket World Cups. Legendary players such as Sachin Tendulkar and MS Dhoni contributed greatly to its success. Cricket is the most popular sport in India.

